    Button label whitelist v2 — frozen for Free 1.0 per Art. 11a(2) CRD.
    Source of truth: _research/button-labels-v1.md (do not edit here without legal re-review).

    Phase-10 (2026-04-29): expanded from 17 to 22 entries (en_EU fallback + 21
    language-specific). Country-variant rows (de_AT, de_BE, fr_BE, fr_LU, nl_BE,
    sv_FI) removed — handled at runtime by Model\Locale\LocaleFallbackResolver
    chain. New languages (bg, cs, el, et, hr, hu, lt, lv, ro, sk, sl) added with
    AI-drafted labels pending counsel review (deadline 2026-05-15).

    Sidebar derivation rule (for legal reviewers):
    The <sidebar> label is the <step1> label with the locative deictic removed:
      "here" / "ici" / "tästä" / "här" / "her" / "qui" / "aquí" / "tutaj" / "aqui"
      / "тук" / "zde" / "εδώ" / "siit" / "ovdje" / "itt" / "čia" / "šeit" / "aici" / "tu" / "tukaj".
    The verb + direct object are preserved verbatim from step1; only the deictic pointer
    that presumes co-location with the CTA button is dropped, since the sidebar link
    renders in a persistent menu rather than next to the order in question.
-->
